TITLE: Detecting Empty Password Accounts in OSSEC
DESCRIPTION: OSSEC rule that searches for accounts with empty passwords in the /etc/shadow file. This check satisfies PCI-DSS requirement 10.2.5 and is a critical security control.

LANGUAGE: ossec
CODE:
```
[CIS - RHEL6 - X.X.X - Account with empty password present {PCI_DSS: 10.2.5}] [any] [https://benchmarks.cisecurity.org/tools2/linux/CIS_Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_6_Benchmark_v1.3.0.pdf]
f:/etc/shadow -> r:^\w+::;
```

