TITLE: Detecting Non-root Accounts with UID 0 in OSSEC
DESCRIPTION: OSSEC rule to check for non-root accounts with UID 0 in /etc/passwd. This is a critical security check that identifies privilege escalation vulnerabilities where regular accounts have root-level access.

LANGUAGE: ossec
CODE:
```
[CIS - RHEL5 - 9.2.5 - Non-root account with uid 0 {CIS: 9.2.5 RHEL5} {PCI_DSS: 10.2.5}] [any] [https://benchmarks.cisecurity.org/tools2/linux/CIS_Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_5_Benchmark_v2.1.0.pdf]
f:/etc/passwd -> !r:^# && !r:^root: && r:^\w+:\w+:0:;
```

