TITLE: Checking SSH Protocol Version Configuration
DESCRIPTION: Detects if SSH is configured to allow Protocol version 1, which is insecure, as per CIS-RHEL6 section 6.2.1. This check examines the SSH daemon configuration to ensure only secure protocol versions are in use for PCI DSS compliance.

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
f:/etc/ssh/sshd_config -> !r:^# && r:Protocol\.+1;
```

