DESCRIPTION: OSSEC rule that checks for non-root accounts with UID 0 in the /etc/passwd file, which is a serious security risk. This rule implements CIS benchmark 9.2.5 for RHEL6 and satisfies PCI-DSS requirement 10.2.5.

LANGUAGE: ossec
CODE:
```
[CIS - RHEL6 - 9.2.5 - Non-root account with uid 0 {CIS: 9.2.5 RHEL6} {PCI_DSS: 10.2.5}] [any] [https://benchmarks.cisecurity.org/tools2/linux/CIS_Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux_6_Benchmark_v1.3.0.pdf]
